==Japanese==
===Verb===
[[泳]]ぐ ([[およぐ]], [[oyogu]])

#to [[swim]].

===Related terms===
*[[蛙泳ぎ]] ([[かえるおよぎ]], ''[[kaeruoyogi]]''): [[breaststroke]].
*[[平泳ぎ]] ([[ひらおよぎ]], ''[[hiraoyogi]]''): [[breaststroke]].
*[[背泳ぎ]] ([[せおよぎ]], ''[[seoyogi]]''): [[backstroke]].
*[[横泳ぎ]] ([[よこおよぎ]], ''[[yokooyogi]]''): [[sidestroke]].
*[[立ち泳ぎ]], [[立泳ぎ]] ([[たちおよぎ]], ''[[tachioyogi]]''): [[tread water|treading water]].

===Idioms===
*[[泳げる様になる]] (およげるようになる, ''oyogeru yō ni naru'') <!-- Is this really an idiom?  -->
*[[時流に乗って泳ぐ]] (じりゅうにのっておよぐ, ''jiryū ni notte oyogu''): to go with the flow.  [[Metaphor]].  Note that [[時流]] ([[じりゅう]], ''[[jiryū]]'') means [[fashion]] or [[trend]], and thus this phrase does not mean to literally "swim with the current" as in a river.  
*[[人波を泳ぐ]] (ひとなみをおよぐ, ''hitonami o oyogu''): to wade through a crowd.

